description: {"blocks":[{"key":"79vd8","text":"This protocol outlines a method of simultaneously measuring the expression of up to 80 genes in any one sample using the QuantiGene multiplex assay from ThermoFisher. This protocol was adapted from the lab of Professor Gill Bates. Cells are grown in 96-well plates, lysed, snap frozen and stored at -80oC. Lysed samples are then incubated overnight with magnetic capture beads as well as a probe panel to detect a custom designed set of genes. A series of incubations and washes amplify the captured RNA signals, which are subsequently measured using a fluorescent probe on a Magpix (Luminex).
